words.def: Actuator – a motor that translates control signals into mechanical movement.
words.name: Actuator

words.def: Ammeter – an instrument that is used to measure current.
words.name: Ammeter

words.def: Ampere – amp, a unit that describes the rate of flow of electricity (current).
words.name: Ampere

words.def: Artificial intelligence – the intelligence of machines and the branch of computer science that aims to create it.
words.name: Artificial intelligence

words.def: Automaton – an early self-operating robot, performing exactly the same actions, over and over.
words.name: Automaton

words.def: Autonomous vehicle - a vehicle equipped with an autopilot system, which is capable of driving from one point to another without input from a human operator.
words.name: Autonomous vehicle

words.def: Compiler – a computer program that translates a high-level language into machine language.
words.name: Compiler

words.def: Degrees of freedom – the extent to which a robot can move itself.
words.name: Degrees of freedom

words.def: Delta robot – a tripod linkage, used to construct fast-acting manipulators with a wide range of movement.
words.name: Delta robot

words.def: FIRST , or For Inspiration and Recognition of Science and Technology - is an organization founded by inventor Dean Kamen in 1989 in order to develop ways to inspire students in engineering and technology fields.
words.name: FIRST

words.def: Haptic – tactile feedback technology using the operator's sense of touch. Also sometimes applied to robot manipulators with their own touch sensitivity.
words.name: Haptic

words.def: Hexapod (platform)- a movable platform using six linear actuators. Often used in flight simulators they also have applications as a robotic manipulator.
words.name: Hexapod

words.def: Hexapod (walker) - a six-legged walking robot, using a simple insect-like locomotion.
words.name: Hexapod

words.def: Hydraulics – the control of mechanical force and movement, generated by the application of liquid under pressure.
words.name: Hydraulics

words.def: Impedance- is the measure of the opposition that a circuit presents to the passage of a current when a voltage is applied.
words.name: Impedance

words.def: Kalman filter – a mathematical technique to estimate the value of a sensor measurement, from a series of intermittent and noisy values.
words.name: Kalman filter

words.def: Linear actuator -- a form of motor that generates a linear movement directly.
words.name: Linear actuator

words.def: Pneumatics – the control of mechanical force and movement, generated by the application of compressed gas.
words.name: Pneumatics

words.def: Robonaut – a development project conducted by NASA to create humanoid robots capable of using space tools and working in similar environments to suited astronauts.
words.name: Robonaut

words.def: Servo – a motor that moves to and maintains a set position under command, rather than continuously moving.
words.name: Servo

words.def: Servomechanism – an automatic device that uses error-sensing negative feedback to correct the performance of a mechanism.
words.name: Servomechanism

words.def: Stewart platform – a movable platform using six linear actuators, hence also known as a Hexapod.
words.name: Stewart platform

words.def: Subsumption architecture – a robot architecture that uses a modular, bottom-up design beginning with the least complex behavioral tasks.
words.name: Subsumption architecture

words.def: Surgical robot – a remote manipulator used for keyhole surgery
words.name: Surgical robot
